					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Parchment codex of the 15th century.</p>
						<objectDesc form="codex">
							<supportDesc material="perg">
								<support>Parchment codex.</support>
								<extent>273 folios<dimensions unit="mm" type="leaf">
										<height>300</height>
										<width>245</width>
									</dimensions>
									<dimensions type="written" unit="mm">
										<height>185</height>
										<width>155</width>
									</dimensions>
								</extent>
								<foliation>
									<p>273 folios (+ 4 unfoliated modern flyleaves at the beginning and 2 older and 4 modern unfoliated paper flyleaves at the end).</p>
								</foliation>
								<collation>
									<p>34 quires: i-xvi8 (folios 1-128), xvii8-1 (folios 129-135), xviii-xxv8 (folios 136-199), xxvi10 (folios 200-209), xxvii-xxxiv8 (folios 210-273). </p>
									<p>Catchwords. </p>
									<p>On guards.</p>
								</collation>
							</supportDesc>
							<layoutDesc>
								<layout columns="2" ruledLines="26" writtenLines="26">
									<p>Uniform layout. </p>
									<p>Masorah magna in usually two lines of the upper and three lines of the lower margin. </p>
									<p>Hair side and flesh side distinguishable. Ruling with hard-point visible.</p>
									<p>The Former and the Latter Prophets separated by two leaves containing a masoretic list.</p>
								</layout>
							</layoutDesc>
						</objectDesc>
						<handDesc hands="1">
							<summary>Sefardi square script, partially punctuated, of the 15th century. <name type="person" role="scribe">Shemu᾿el ben Shemu᾿el ibn Musa</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon, Lisbon, <date calendar="Hebrew">5243</date> [<date calendar="Gregorian">1483</date>] (see volume 3, Or 2628, folio 185v). </summary>
							<handNote script="Hebrew" scope="major"/>
						</handDesc>
						<decoDesc>
							<summary>20 full borders sometimes accompanied with decorated initial-word panels, in colours and gold. 4 decorated initial-word panels.</summary>
							<decoNote type="border">20 full borders sometimes accompanied with decorated initial-word panels, in colours and gold. <locus n="1v, 134r, 134v, 135r, 135v, 136v, 168r, 210r, 246r, 250v, 252r, 256r, 256v, 258r, 260v, 261v, 263r, 264v, 265v, 271v"/>
							</decoNote>
							<decoNote type="initial">4 decorated initial-word panels.<locus n="1v, 21r, 40r, 85v"/>
							</decoNote>
						</decoDesc>
						<additions>
							<p>
								<name type="person" role="patron">Yosef ben Yudah called Elhakhim</name>: inscribed with his name in the colophon (see volume 3, Or 2628, folio 185v). </p>
						</additions>
						<bindingDesc>
							<binding>
								<p>BM in-house. Green leather, gold-tooled Star of David on the inner and outer cover.</p>
								<p>Spine title: 'Hebrew Bible. Lisbon 1484-53. Former and Latter Prophets. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2627.'</p>
							</binding>
